   <head>[Lines on Dr Robert Smith]</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Do you ask why old Focus Silvanus defies,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|--+|--+" line_length="9">And leaves not a chestnut in being?</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">'Tis not that old Focus himself has got eyes,</l>
     <l n="4" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">But because he has writ about seeing.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
